[Crimean-Congo hemorrhagic fever (CCHF) is a tick-borne viral disease that causes a fatal hemorrhagic illness in humans. This disease is asymptomatic in animals (https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/25229708).

CCHF was first confirmed in Gujarat state, in a nosocomial outbreak in 2011. Cases have occurred recently in Gujarat state, which shares a border with Rajasthan state. Jodhpur district is a district in the state of Rajasthan in western India (https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Jodhpur_district). - Mod.UBA

